text: I'm sick to death of seeing street racing movies with all these new Euro sports cars in them. Street racers don't drive those cars. Posh people who sip tea and own race horses drive those cars. Street racing is about back alley gambling on cars and doing your own modifications with the money you earned from street racing and not the money you got off of your grandfather when he passed away. What happened to Japanese imports? These new street racing movies all seem to be about showing off the movie budget by using all these cars and making them explode. They've become more about action and special effects than actual street racing. This movie should be called Need to make more explosions for our obscene paychecks.

text: I finally watched this, and I think it was awesome. At first. But after some minutes of thinking, I realized that this movie is just disgusting. How many lives did these guys risk only to win a stupid race for money? How many family man died in car accidents caused by the main characters. Maybe that fat cop in the car has a son or daughter, and he promised them that they will go to the beach or the zoo on the weekend... but then there was some billionare assholes, who had to make an illegal race and risk the lives of everyone on the streets, because it's so fucking fun, and the money is good if you win.. so I guess the kids have to go on their own to the beach.. oh wait, they will go to the funeral of their father.  So after all: this movie is about rich douchebags who have no responsibility and don't give a fuck about other's lives. It's nice, isn't it. :) Yeah, I know that this is just a movie based on a video game, and I should not look at it the way I did, but I think that's normal way to look at things. :(
